            "question_text": "show that \\(2x + 1 = 6y - 4\\).",
            "solution_text": "\\(5^{2x+1} = 25^{3y-2}\\)\n\\(5^{2x+1} = (5^2)^{3y-2}\\)\n\\(5^{2x+1} = 5^{2(3y-2)}\\)\n\\(5^{2x+1} = 5^{6y-4}\\)\nEquating the powers, we have:\n\\(2x + 1 = 6y - 4\\)"
